The invention relates to the technical field of metallurgy, in particular to a converter steelmaking dephosphorization agent. The converter steelmaking dephosphorization agent is characterized in that the melting point is less than or equal to 1,280 DEG C; the converter steelmaking dephosphorization agent comprises the following components in percentage by weight: 60.0 to 75.0 percent of Fe2O3, 20.0 to 35.0 percent of CaO, and less than or equal to 5.0 percent of impurities; and the impurities comprise MgO, Al2O3, MnO, SiO2, K2O, Na2O and the like. A preparation method of the converter steelmaking dephosphorization agent comprises the following steps of: cracking the raw materials into particles with the granularity of 0 to 10mm; after uniformly mixing the particles, smelting the mixture at a high temperature of 1,350 to 1,400 DEG C to generate blocky materials, wherein in the mineralogical phase structure of the generated blocky materials, 2CaO.Fe2O3 serves as a main phase; and cooling the blocky materials and cracking the blocky materials into particle blocks with the granularity of 3 to 40mm. A using method of the converter steelmaking dephosphorization agent is that in the steelmaking process of a converter, 8 to 10 kg of converter steelmaking dephosphorization agents are added per ton of steel; the dephosphorization rate of the converter steelmaking dephosphorization agent can reach over 90 percent; and the phosphorus content in the steel can be effectively controlled in the range of 0.004 percent. The converter steelmaking dephosphorization agent has the beneficial effects that the converter steelmaking dephosphorization agent has high dephosphorization efficiency, is stable, does not contain fluoride and has no pollution to the environment.
