The invention relates to a metallurgical auxiliary material fluxing agent and a preparation method thereof. The metallurgical auxiliary material fluxing agent is characterized by comprising the following components in percentage by weight: 60 to 75 percent of ferric oxide (Fe2O), 20 to 35 percent of calcium oxide (CaO) and less than or equal to 5.0 percent of total impurities. The preparation method comprises: crushing the components of the metallurgical auxiliary material fluxing agent into particles of a particle size of less than 20 millimeters; uniformly mixing, smelting at a high temperature of 1,350 to 1,400 DEG C, and melting and reacting to obtain a blocky material with an ore phase structure which takes 2CaO.Fe2O3 as a main phase; and cooling the blocky material, and processing the blocky material to obtain 200-mesh powder. The using method of the metallurgical auxiliary material fluxing agent comprises: adding the fluxing agent in an amount which is 4 to 6 percent (for best fluxing effect) based on the weight of agglomerate or converter reduced pellets; and uniformly mixing. Compared with the prior art, the metallurgical auxiliary material fluxing agent and the preparation method have the advantages that: the valuable slag making material (CaO) and an iron material (TFe) which can be reduced into iron are fully utilized; the melting point is less than or equal to 1,280 DEG C, which is lower than that of fluorite and therefore is favorable for fluxing of auxiliary materials, and the fluxing effect is stable; and environment pollution is avoided.
